 b -RRB- Withdrawal According to international law , any State is , in principle , entitled to withdraw from a Treaty , by   following   the withdrawal procedure of such Treaty . Document CD/1777 , article VII states that each Party has the right to withdraw from the treaty , if it decides that extraordinary events , related to the matter of the treaty , have jeopardized its supreme interests , by giving notice of such withdrawal in writing to the depositary , no less than three months in advance of the date of withdrawal from the treaty .
