 -LRB- 1 -RRB- None of the provisions contained in either the 1969 or the 1986 Vienna Conventions is useful or specific with regard to questions relating to the formulation and communication of a withdrawal . However , it is abundantly clear from the travaux prparatoires of the 1969 Convention that , as in the case of the formulation of objections and the formulation of reservations , the procedure to be followed in withdrawing unilateral declarations must be identical to that   followed   when withdrawing a reservation . -LRB- 2 -RRB- It therefore seemed prudent to the Commission simply to take note , within the framework of the Guide to Practice , of this procedural parallelism between the withdrawal of a reservation and the withdrawal of an objection , which holds for the authority competent to make the withdrawal at the international level and the consequences -LRB- or , rather , the absence of consequences -RRB- of the violation of the rules of internal law at the time of formulation and those of notification and communication of the withdrawal .
