 Immunities or special procedural rules which may attach to the official capacity of a person , whether under national or international law , shall not bar the Court from exercising its jurisdiction over such a person . This provision   follows   in the wake of Article 7 of the 1945 London Charter , which reads : The official position of defendants , whether as Heads of State or responsible officials in Government Departments , shall not be considered as freeing them from responsibility or mitigating punishment .
