 The reason for the rule of law spanning all areas of rule-making has been aptly summed up by Mario Monti , the European Union 's competition commissioner : Effective judicial review is the ultimate guarantor of accountability . Accountability requires safeguards against selectiveness , whereby parts of law are   followed   while others are flouted . Thus , school fees in primary education may be charged or teachers ' trade union freedoms denied in breach of international and domestic law , undermining the very notion of the rule of law .
